value: Breeds on the larger islands in the eastern Mediterranean (Cyprus and possibly Crete), Syria, Palestine, and Egypt; Africa south of the Sahara from Senegal to Ethiopia, and south to Nigeria, the southern limit of the Savanna belt in central Africa, Lake Edward and Tanganyika Terri- tory.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Resident, dry areas near water: Sahara Desert to S Mauritania - N Tanzania; down Nile to Mediterranean coast, excluding NE Somalia.
Senegambia to Red Sea, ne Tanzania and e Mediterranean
usually on dry ground but rarely far from water;inhabits cultivated fields, burnt grassland near poolws, lakes, rivers or lagoons, or mudflats, sandflats, rice fields, flooded fields, beaches & dunes
